goblin-repl
===========

Embeds an interactive Goblin REPL into any web page using WebAssembly.
Readers can run live Goblin code right in the browser — no server required.


INSTALLATION
------------

Copy the entire goblin_repl folder into your project's glams/ directory:

    your-project/
      glams/
        goblin_repl/
          glam.toml
          README
          goblin-repl.gbln
          js/
            goblin-repl.js
          wasm/
            goblin_wasm.js
            goblin_wasm_bg.wasm


CONFIGURATION
-------------

Open glam.toml and fill in the [needs] section with Box variables from
your box.toml or goblin box dump:

    [needs]
    output_dir = "#site::public_dir"

  output_dir   The directory where the WASM and JS files will be copied.
               Must be publicly accessible from the browser.


USAGE
-----

Import the glam:

    use goblin_repl

Copy assets to your output directory:

    goblin-repl::init()

Replace GOBLIN_REPL::EMBED tokens in a string:

    result | goblin-repl::apply_tokens(body)

Place the token anywhere in your content:

    GOBLIN_REPL::EMBED


ACTIONS
-------

  goblin-repl::init()
    Copies goblin-repl.js, goblin_wasm.js, and goblin_wasm_bg.wasm
    into output_dir. Call this once before serving any pages.

  goblin-repl::apply_tokens(body)
    Takes a string. Replaces every occurrence of GOBLIN_REPL::EMBED
    with the REPL embed HTML. Returns the updated string.


TOKENS
------

  GOBLIN_REPL::EMBED
    Place this anywhere you want a REPL to appear.
    Resolved by goblin-repl::apply_tokens.


WHAT THE READER SEES
--------------------

A dark terminal panel with:
  - Scrollable output area
  - Single-line input with a > prompt
  - Arrow keys for input history
  - Multi-line block support (type a block, close with xx)
  - A reset button to clear the session

Each REPL on a page has its own independent session.


INCLUDED FILES
--------------

  js/goblin-repl.js        The REPL UI. Mounts into the page, loads the
                           WASM, handles all input and output.

  wasm/goblin_wasm.js      WebAssembly glue. Loaded by the browser at runtime.

  wasm/goblin_wasm_bg.wasm The compiled Goblin VM. Runs entirely in the browser.
